   Scheduled Services

   Listed below are the scheduled services provided by the Department of
   Public Works (DPW) and the District Division of Transportation (DDOT).
   Please click on any of the services below. Each link provides a
   detailed description of each service, scheduled response times, and
   procedures to address the occurrence of missed services.

   You can request any of the following services by calling the Mayor's
   Citywide Call Center at (202) 727-1000 or completing a service request
   online using the District government's Citizen Service Request Form.

   These are the scheduled services provided by the Department of Public
   Works (DPW) and District Division of Transportation (DDOT):


     * Abandoned Auto (Private Property)
     * Abandoned Auto (Public Space)
     * Alley Cleaning
     * Alley Repair
     * Autumn Leaf Collection
     * Bulk Collection
     * Dead Animal Pick-Up
     * Grass & Weed Mowing
     * Illegal Dumping
     * Litter Cans (Repair)
     * Litter Cans (Request for Installation)
     * Litter Cans (Service)
     * Parking Enforcement
     * Pothole
     * Rat Abatement


     * Recycling Bins
     * Recycling Collection
     * Sanitation Enforcement
     * Sidewalk Repair
     * Street Cleaning (Manual - Unscheduled)
     * Street Cleaning (Sweeper - Scheduled)
     * Streetlight/Alley Light
     * Street Repair
     * Street Sign
     * Supercan
     * Supercan Repairs
     * Traffic Signals
     * Trash Collection
     * Tree Related
     * Yard Waste


